{"key":"processedPost-9590592","value":{"id":9590592,"first":9589586,"last":9601663,"when":1231719399,"utime":"01/12/09 02:16 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I was hoping to eliminate fanning and spraying all together.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />VERY bad idea.&nbsp; Evaporation of moisture from the substrate is a major pinning trigger.&nbsp; If you want good performance, the substrate must dry out between mistings.&nbsp; That takes eyeball and hand work.&nbsp; There is no automated system that can read your cakes to know when to mist.<br /><br />Build a shotgun terrarium per the tek and your humidity will be above 90%, guaranteed.&nbsp; If your hygrometer reads less than that, calibrate it.<br /><br />Get the terrarium off the table and set it on blocks so the air can enter from the bottom.&nbsp; Otherwise, the blocked holes down there do nothing and that's your major intake source.<br />RR","title":"Re: First larger terrarium set-up (pics)","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}